WEBVTT

00:28.243 --> 00:30.143
Hey, Jeffrey. How are you?

00:30.312 --> 00:32.302
Hey, Jeffrey.

00:42.658 --> 00:44.125
Will you excuse me?

00:48.230 --> 00:50.460
That looks like a powerful scope.

00:50.866 --> 00:52.493
It was my dad's.

00:53.769 --> 00:57.170
I can't tell you how many times
I found your dad right here...

00:57.339 --> 01:01.366
...right here, sitting there
looking through that thing.

01:03.679 --> 01:05.772
Seymour...

01:05.948 --> 01:07.779
...if I can lose my dad...

01:07.950 --> 01:11.818
...then what's to say
I can't lose my mom too?

01:13.989 --> 01:17.481
I don't know why
this thing happened, kid...

01:17.693 --> 01:19.888
...but I do know your father loved you.

01:20.362 --> 01:24.856
And I'm sure he's up there
right now watching out for you.

01:27.569 --> 01:29.730
You do right by him, Jeffrey.

01:30.305 --> 01:32.637
You look after your mother...

01:32.808 --> 01:36.175
...and you become a man
that he would be proud of.

01:38.013 --> 01:40.413
-What happened? Are you all right?
-Yeah, I'm okay.

01:40.582 --> 01:43.312
Don't worry, you've got plenty of time.
You'll get there.

01:55.531 --> 01:56.555
Bye, honey!

02:01.436 --> 02:03.768
Hey, where you going?

02:03.939 --> 02:05.304
Kiss your mom goodbye?

02:13.482 --> 02:14.847
Oh!

02:20.322 --> 02:21.311
Ooh.

02:23.659 --> 02:24.853
What a loser.

02:36.138 --> 02:37.833
What do you call that?

02:44.313 --> 02:46.474
Oh, my God.

03:09.404 --> 03:10.666
Oh.

03:13.208 --> 03:15.039
Jeffrey?

03:15.777 --> 03:17.574
-Jeffrey?
What do you want?

03:17.746 --> 03:20.772
It's Jean-Paul. Something's wrong.

03:20.949 --> 03:23.417
It's just like he's, you know,
like not normal.

03:23.585 --> 03:25.553
Just not normal.

03:26.755 --> 03:28.950
For the love of Mike, what happened?

03:29.124 --> 03:31.490
He was just like this when I found.... Oh....

03:31.660 --> 03:34.060
There you go, Jean-Paul.
It's gonna be okay.

03:34.229 --> 03:37.289
Sure it is, sure it is, yeah.

03:38.400 --> 03:39.662
Oh.

03:40.769 --> 03:43.636
-No.
-Oh, Jeffrey. Oh, Jeffrey.

03:43.805 --> 03:47.297
Oh, sweetie. Don't-- Jeffrey.

03:47.809 --> 03:49.037
Oh.

03:49.745 --> 03:52.043
That's nice for Jean-Paul.

03:55.550 --> 03:59.748
Well, oh, dear. Tsk. Bye-bye.

03:59.922 --> 04:02.117
Let's go, sweetie.

04:02.291 --> 04:05.419
Sometimes it takes a great tragedy...

04:05.594 --> 04:08.062
...to make a man see his life clearly.

04:09.932 --> 04:13.766
I realize in my 29 years on this planet...

04:13.936 --> 04:18.373
...I haven't told you often enough
how much I appreciate you.

04:18.540 --> 04:24.775
But you are all I have left
in this cruel world.

04:25.347 --> 04:29.579
And I'm not going to let anything
come between us.

04:29.751 --> 04:31.742
-Oh....
-Ever.

04:32.621 --> 04:36.182
-I love you.
-I love you too.

04:37.426 --> 04:39.587
Thank you, sweetie, love you.

04:39.761 --> 04:42.855
But you know what, honey?
We really have to get going, we're late.

04:43.198 --> 04:44.825
I can see that my time is almost up.

04:45.000 --> 04:47.468
So I want to share with you
one final story.

04:47.636 --> 04:51.800
On a beautiful morning in 1998...

04:51.974 --> 04:55.000
...I went to my doctor
for a routine colonoscopy.

04:55.177 --> 04:59.307
He ran some tests to make sure
I didn't have cancer...

04:59.481 --> 05:01.039
...but I did.

05:03.218 --> 05:06.210
I tried every treatment
known to Western medicine...

05:10.859 --> 05:14.727
...and some unknown
to Western medicine.

05:18.233 --> 05:20.292
Whoo! Ha-ha-ha.

05:21.636 --> 05:23.763
Nothing worked.

05:24.473 --> 05:27.306
I was told I was....

05:27.909 --> 05:31.777
I was told I was going to die
in six months.

05:32.914 --> 05:35.781
That was six years ago.

05:35.951 --> 05:38.476
I beat cancer.

05:39.921 --> 05:41.582
How?

05:41.757 --> 05:43.281
With my mind.

05:43.458 --> 05:46.791
I decided I was not gonna let
some overactive clump of cells...

05:46.962 --> 05:49.226
...stop me from living my life.

05:49.398 --> 05:54.563
From that moment on, I realized
I could have anything my heart desired.

05:54.736 --> 05:56.203
You can too.

05:56.371 --> 06:00.569
Remember, you are the author
of your own life story.

06:00.742 --> 06:04.473
Why not make it a happy ending?
Thank you.

06:08.183 --> 06:09.707
Oh.

06:16.124 --> 06:18.718
<i>One, two, three, four!</i>

06:35.077 --> 06:38.444
-Son-of-a--
-Good morning, Jeffrey.

06:38.613 --> 06:42.344
That's Mr. Mannus to you,
and there's nothing good about it.

06:42.517 --> 06:44.212
Jeffrey...

06:45.454 --> 06:47.979
...did you change the window display?

06:49.925 --> 06:52.052
Sex sells, Seymour.

06:52.227 --> 06:54.889
Change it back, now!

06:55.063 --> 06:57.429
I'm putting Keith in charge
of window displays.

06:57.599 --> 07:00.363
-What?
-I need someone I can count on.

07:00.535 --> 07:03.629
Seymour, how long
have I been employed here?

07:03.805 --> 07:05.067
Thirteen years.

07:05.240 --> 07:08.403
Yeah. And in all that time,
have I ever missed a day of work?

07:08.577 --> 07:12.775
Yes. More than any employee I ever had.

07:12.948 --> 07:15.576
There was the day your ant farm broke...

07:15.750 --> 07:19.686
...the day you lost your hat,
the day you had a sore tongue.

07:19.855 --> 07:22.585
I can't do my job if I can't enunciate.

07:22.757 --> 07:24.884
Jeffrey, I like you.

07:25.060 --> 07:27.722
I liked your father,
he was a good friend...

07:27.896 --> 07:30.057
...and a great Rotarian.

07:30.232 --> 07:33.759
But I need you to start
taking this job seriously.

07:34.769 --> 07:38.398
Just behave or you're fired.

07:38.573 --> 07:40.598
You know, positivity goes back centuries.

07:40.775 --> 07:45.109
I mean, Jesus, Jesus, for crying out loud,
was a motivational speaker.

07:45.280 --> 07:46.907
-I mean, at his core.
-I guess, yeah.

07:47.082 --> 07:48.106
--talk to him.

07:48.283 --> 07:51.218
I haven't done anything like that in years.
What do I say to him?

07:51.386 --> 07:55.618
Just ask him a question. You could
ask him a follow-up about his colon.

07:55.790 --> 07:59.123
This is utterly ridiculous.
I have a lot of work to do. I'm just gonna--

07:59.294 --> 08:01.558
Ask him anything,
because here's the point:

08:01.730 --> 08:04.893
You can't spend
the rest of your Friday nights...

08:05.066 --> 08:07.034
...playing Scrabble with that son of yours.

08:07.202 --> 08:09.727
-I know.
-You gotta dip your toe in the water.

08:09.905 --> 08:12.897
Somehow, some way,
some dipping must occur.

08:13.074 --> 08:15.065
Stop talking about-- Okay, okay.

08:15.243 --> 08:17.643
-Calm down, relax. It'll be easy.
-Okay, I'm mature.

08:17.812 --> 08:20.337
The third world's a region
I'd like to get my hands on.

08:20.515 --> 08:23.006
-They could use some positivity.
-Hi.

08:23.185 --> 08:24.777
-Hi.
-Excuse me, gentlemen.

08:24.953 --> 08:27.444
-H--
-Hi.

08:28.623 --> 08:31.786
I don't want to interrupt anything,
of course, but I was wondering...

08:31.960 --> 08:36.020
-...if it's all right if I ask you a question?
-Sure. Absolutely.

08:38.832 --> 08:41.529
Stem cells, that's what I mean.

08:41.703 --> 08:46.037
It's like, what do you think of the stem-cell
research that's going on today?

08:47.275 --> 08:50.369
I'm no expert, but I think
if it helps the human race, go for it.

08:50.545 --> 08:52.103
Good. Good answer.

08:52.280 --> 08:53.941
Oh. Thank you.

08:54.115 --> 08:56.140
-Jan Mannus, right?
-Me. Yes, I'm Jan.

08:56.318 --> 08:59.845
Associate Director of Human Resources.
You are doing a hell of a job.

09:00.021 --> 09:01.818
Thank you for noticing.

09:01.990 --> 09:04.049
-Hmm.
-Anyway....

09:05.727 --> 09:08.992
-Okay.
-Do you like, uh, jazz?

09:09.164 --> 09:10.188
Yes.

09:10.365 --> 09:11.764
-Do you?
-I love jazz.

09:11.933 --> 09:13.992
You lo--?
Well, I play in a band...

09:14.169 --> 09:18.868
...and we gig on Friday nights
at the Jazz Odyssey.

09:19.040 --> 09:20.268
Yes, I know that place.

09:20.442 --> 09:23.070
Do you? Good.
Would you like to come with me?

09:23.245 --> 09:26.180
I'd love to come with you.
That's the most wonderful invitation.

09:26.348 --> 09:27.838
-Thank you.
-Terrific.

09:28.950 --> 09:32.818
But I'm afraid I can't on Friday night.

09:32.988 --> 09:36.890
-I'm sorry. What did you say?
-I said I can't make it Friday night.

09:37.058 --> 09:38.753
I'm still not understanding you...

09:38.927 --> 09:41.862
...because the word "can't"
isn't in my vocabulary.

09:43.932 --> 09:48.232
You see, Jan, we never regret
the things in life we do...

09:48.403 --> 09:51.566
...only the things we don't.

09:52.407 --> 09:54.466
-I wrote that.
-Ah.

09:55.010 --> 09:56.034
I do.

09:58.213 --> 10:01.080
I do, but you know what I mean,
not like the whole "I do."

10:01.249 --> 10:02.773
I mean, what I'm saying is yes.

10:02.951 --> 10:05.681
I would like to go with you...

10:05.854 --> 10:08.982
...and listen to you play the jazz.

10:13.028 --> 10:15.519
-Hi, sweetheart.
-What are you doing here?

10:15.697 --> 10:17.597
I thought I'd give you a ride home.

10:17.766 --> 10:21.725
Guess who I ran into yesterday?
Jennifer Cushman's mother.

10:21.903 --> 10:24.167
Jennifer Cushman
is apparently getting a divorce.

10:24.339 --> 10:25.772
-Good for her.
-I know.

10:25.940 --> 10:30.343
She'll be at the church's single mixer
on Friday so I thought you might wanna go.

10:30.512 --> 10:32.537
I have plans with you Friday night,
remember?

10:32.714 --> 10:33.976
Oh, right.

10:34.149 --> 10:37.118
Why are you so concerned
about my personal life all of a sudden?

10:37.285 --> 10:40.812
You haven't been on a date in three years,
Jeffrey. I'm concerned about--

10:40.989 --> 10:42.513
Neither have you.

10:42.691 --> 10:44.352
Well, I got asked out today, and....

10:44.526 --> 10:47.495
-Pfft. Please.
-What do you mean, "Please"?

10:47.662 --> 10:50.062
Can you--?
What is wrong with me getting asked out?

10:50.231 --> 10:52.358
-You're a middle-aged widow.
-I'm not that old.

10:52.534 --> 10:54.627
Not some trollop
out of a Jackie Collins novel.

10:54.803 --> 10:57.772
There's no reason to be absolutely ugly
to me in front of people.

10:57.939 --> 11:01.067
I'm trying to protect you. What if
it doesn't work out, like the last one?

11:01.242 --> 11:03.642
I couldn't bear to see you get hurt again.

11:03.812 --> 11:08.340
You know something, we never regret
the things that we actually do in our lives...

11:08.516 --> 11:11.417
...only the things that we don't do. So.

11:11.586 --> 11:14.111
Where did you get
that pseudo-philosophical platitude?

11:14.289 --> 11:16.120
-It doesn't matter.
-Dr. Phil?

11:16.291 --> 11:18.987
Okay, that's not funny.
I think I'm gonna go.

11:19.160 --> 11:21.128
Okay, fine.

11:21.296 --> 11:24.459
So. When is this date?

11:25.133 --> 11:29.035
-Friday night.
-What? That's Putt-Putt night.

11:29.204 --> 11:32.799
But I said I was sorry.
-Well, I'm afraid sorry won't do.

11:32.974 --> 11:35.408
I know, I know, sweetheart.

11:35.577 --> 11:39.775
What if I make your favorite, huh?
What do you think? Little bitty?

11:39.948 --> 11:42.212
No! You can't win back my affection
with Manwich.

11:42.384 --> 11:45.285
This has been the worst day of my life.
I'm going to my room.

12:28.663 --> 12:31.188
Did you do something to your hair?

12:31.366 --> 12:33.129
I cut it.

12:35.503 --> 12:38.995
A little garish,
but not altogether unattractive.

12:39.174 --> 12:42.666
-Really?
-What's the occasion?

12:42.844 --> 12:45.506
Well, I have a date tonight, remember?

12:46.381 --> 12:48.941
Oh, yes, right, of course.

12:49.117 --> 12:52.245
The bitter sting of rejection's
coming back to me now.

12:52.420 --> 12:55.253
Jeffrey. Oh, my goodness, here it is.

12:55.423 --> 12:56.856
Well, have a nice day.

12:57.025 --> 12:59.516
-Aren't you forgetting something?
-What?

12:59.694 --> 13:02.629
It comes in a brown paper sack,
and rhymes with my lunch.

13:02.797 --> 13:04.958
I just didn't have time
to make it this morning.

13:05.133 --> 13:08.660
Why can't you just grab yourself
a little sandwich or something?

13:08.837 --> 13:12.534
All right, honey? Bye-bye, bye-bye.
There you go.

13:30.158 --> 13:32.126
Can I help you?

13:33.862 --> 13:36.956
Yes. Do you have anything
that's not utterly repugnant?

13:37.131 --> 13:38.393
No.

13:40.168 --> 13:41.999
Okay.

13:42.170 --> 13:45.799
Fine, give me three biscottis...

13:45.974 --> 13:48.135
...two chocolate chip fudge brownies...

13:48.309 --> 13:51.039
...and one of these giant
Rice Krispie abominations.

13:51.212 --> 13:53.180
Maybe a heart attack will teach
my mother...

13:53.348 --> 13:56.340
-...a lesson in abandonment.
-Maybe.

13:56.985 --> 13:58.748
Biscotti.

14:01.890 --> 14:03.289
That's a cool store.

14:03.458 --> 14:08.088
It's actually got some character,
unlike those lame mega-chains.

14:08.263 --> 14:09.821
Do you like working there?

14:09.998 --> 14:13.331
It's paying the bills
until I make my first astronomical discovery.

14:13.501 --> 14:17.164
You're an astronomer?
That's cool.

14:17.772 --> 14:21.208
I'm a singer, actually. Well, trying to be.

14:22.110 --> 14:24.044
Most of my songs
that I write are about...

14:24.212 --> 14:27.204
...how corporate America's
totally screwing up our culture.

14:27.382 --> 14:30.146
I'm calling my first album
"Bed, Bath and Bullshit."

14:30.318 --> 14:31.649
So....

14:31.819 --> 14:36.085
I actually do a show here every Saturday.

14:37.025 --> 14:40.290
It's not sappy. You know,
my songs aren't about love or anything.

14:40.461 --> 14:42.395
They're about...

14:42.564 --> 14:45.431
...how much I hate corporations.

14:45.600 --> 14:50.196
So, anyway, that will be 10.76.

14:50.371 --> 14:54.239
For stale bread and cereal?
That's obscene.

14:54.409 --> 14:58.778
I know. The guys who own this place
are a bunch of poser A-holes.

14:58.947 --> 15:04.351
So.... But I'll give you
my employee discount if you want.

15:05.753 --> 15:08.017
It's 10 dollars even.

15:11.659 --> 15:15.026
All right, here you go.

15:15.930 --> 15:18.398
Well, take it easy.

15:29.344 --> 15:30.641
Here.

15:30.812 --> 15:33.076
This is redeemable for a free book.

15:33.247 --> 15:37.308
Not including first editions
or new releases...

15:37.485 --> 15:40.318
-...or fiction.
-Thanks.

15:41.022 --> 15:42.785
Or non-fiction.

15:45.393 --> 15:47.088
It's--

15:49.897 --> 15:51.990
We--

16:09.651 --> 16:10.640
Woo. Oh.

16:17.925 --> 16:22.089
Thank you. Thank you very much
for coming out to the Jazz Odyssey tonight.

16:22.263 --> 16:26.757
For our last song, I'd like to dedicate it
to a very special lady...

16:26.934 --> 16:29.164
-...in the audience tonight.
-Oh--

16:51.526 --> 16:52.686
Do you mind if I say this?

16:52.860 --> 16:55.727
I just can't get over what
a great singer you are. I mean that.

16:55.897 --> 16:58.798
Well, Nat King Cole,
that's a great singer. I'm just a wannabe.

16:58.966 --> 17:00.399
You know something? I disagree.

17:00.568 --> 17:03.662
To me, I think that you could have
your own Christmas special even.

17:03.838 --> 17:08.638
Thank you. That's very kind. Actually,
music is just another hobby for me.

17:08.810 --> 17:12.507
Kind of like golf
and horseback riding and archery.

17:12.714 --> 17:14.375
And wine making.

17:14.549 --> 17:16.039
-Of course, puppetry.
-Oh.

17:16.217 --> 17:20.085
My goodness. I just don't even understand
how you find time for all of it.

17:20.253 --> 17:23.382
I think we always find time
for the things that are important to us.

17:23.558 --> 17:25.185
Don't we? What's important to you?

17:25.358 --> 17:26.416
-Me?
-Yeah.

17:26.594 --> 17:27.788
Oh, my goodness. Well....

17:27.962 --> 17:30.396
Unless I'm being too personal,
because I don't wanna--

17:30.565 --> 17:32.795
No, not at all.
I just haven't thought about...

17:32.967 --> 17:35.629
...what's important to me
in a really long time, so....

17:35.803 --> 17:37.896
Well, maybe it's time you start.

17:38.072 --> 17:39.801
What a wonderful evening I had.

17:39.974 --> 17:42.033
-You are so nice.
-Well, thank you, I did too.

17:42.210 --> 17:44.405
Would you like to maybe do it again?

17:45.446 --> 17:47.505
-You mean go out again?
-Yeah.

17:47.682 --> 17:50.173
I mean, my God, you're beautiful,
you're smart, and....

17:50.351 --> 17:52.615
Plus, you like my singing, so there's that.

17:52.787 --> 17:55.950
Seriously, though,
I think being a single mother...

17:56.124 --> 17:59.355
...is the most noble thing
that anyone could ever do.

17:59.527 --> 18:03.520
It takes strength and fortitude
to raise a well-adjusted child...

18:03.698 --> 18:06.098
...who is prepared to go out
and take on the world...

18:06.267 --> 18:09.168
...and I think what you've done
is just terrific.

18:09.971 --> 18:11.871
-You know something, Mert?
-Yeah.

18:12.039 --> 18:14.837
-I have to be completely honest with you.
-Mm-hm.

18:15.009 --> 18:17.102
My son lives with me.

18:17.278 --> 18:18.609
Oh.

18:19.347 --> 18:20.814
He's still in school?

18:20.982 --> 18:25.646
He's 29. I know what you're thinking.
He should have his own place hands down.

18:25.820 --> 18:28.983
But, you know,
the thing is we made a big agreement.

18:29.157 --> 18:30.886
That he could live at home
until he makes...

18:31.058 --> 18:32.958
-...his first astronomical discovery.
-Oh.

18:33.327 --> 18:36.262
Astronom-- Wow, that's--
Boy, that sounds ambitious.

18:36.430 --> 18:38.455
-Yeah.
-I'd love to meet him.

18:39.801 --> 18:40.790
Sure, of course.

18:40.968 --> 18:45.234
But you're not talking about now, right?
No, yeah, because he's not actually here.

18:45.406 --> 18:48.136
-It could be another time.
-Okay. Another time, well, good.

18:48.309 --> 18:50.539
Well, listen, I'll call you.

18:50.711 --> 18:52.178
-Oh, okay.
-All right.

18:52.346 --> 18:54.246
Sure. Do that. Whoa. Ha-ha.

18:56.617 --> 18:57.811
-Oh, boy.
-Good night.

18:57.985 --> 18:59.316
Good night.

20:20.301 --> 20:21.791
Jeffrey?

20:21.969 --> 20:23.994
That's my name, don't wear it out.

20:24.171 --> 20:26.401
Well, what are you doing up?

20:26.574 --> 20:29.042
Where did you say you were again?

20:29.210 --> 20:31.701
I told you, sweetie. I was out with Barbara.

20:31.879 --> 20:34.439
-Lie! I called Barbara's house.
-Hah!

20:34.615 --> 20:36.845
Her son told me he was with her all night.

20:37.018 --> 20:40.044
You've been cavorting around
with that Mert character, haven't you?

20:40.221 --> 20:43.349
-Oh, tough.
-I knew it.

20:44.125 --> 20:46.184
Have you had sex with him?

20:46.360 --> 20:49.659
-I'm not going to answer that.
-You have.

20:49.830 --> 20:53.857
Oh. I hope you used a condom.
I'm sure he has herpes.

20:54.035 --> 20:55.263
Oh!

21:00.107 --> 21:02.041
-I want you to meet him.
-Forget it. No!

21:02.209 --> 21:05.610
If you wanna skulk around behind my back
with some VD-ridden sex maniac...

21:05.780 --> 21:09.079
...who keeps you out until
all hours of the night, that's your business.

21:09.250 --> 21:11.684
-But I want nothing to do with him.
-Can't you just...

21:11.852 --> 21:14.582
...make this easier on me for once,
Jeffrey, and meet him?

21:14.755 --> 21:16.313
I'm sorry, but the answer is no.

21:16.490 --> 21:20.085
Come on, sweetie.
We can go to Putt-Putt.

21:20.328 --> 21:21.852
Hmm?

21:22.363 --> 21:23.955
Hmm?

